<Base
  title="Refinance & Property Tax Appraisals in Las Vegas | Las Vegas Appraisal Co."
  description="Refinance and property tax appeal appraisals in Las Vegas. Lender-compliant, FHA-approved. Lower your tax bill or access your equity. Call (702) 894-9279."
  canonical="https://lvappraisalco.com/refinance-tax-appraisals"
>

  <div class="service-page-header">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Refinance & Tax Appraisals</p>
      <h1>Refinance & Property Tax Appraisals in Las Vegas</h1>
      <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.05rem;">
        Maximize your equity. Lower your tax bill.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <div class="service-content">
      <p>Whether you're refinancing your mortgage or challenging a property tax assessment, the appraised value of your home has a direct impact on your finances. Las Vegas Appraisal Co. provides fast, lender-compliant appraisals for refinance transactions and independent appraisals for property tax appeals throughout Clark County.</p>

      <h2>Refinance Appraisals</h2>
      <p>Most lenders require an independent appraisal before approving a refinance or home equity loan. Our certified appraisers produce USPAP-compliant reports that meet the standards of conventional, FHA, and VA lenders. We work directly with homeowners and lenders to deliver accurate, timely reports with fast turnaround.</p>

      <p>If your home has appreciated since your original purchase, a refinance appraisal may help you eliminate private mortgage insurance (PMI), access equity, or qualify for better loan terms.</p>

      <h2>Property Tax Appeal Appraisals</h2>
      <p>Clark County property tax assessments don't always reflect true market value — especially during market corrections or in neighborhoods that haven't seen the same appreciation as the broader Las Vegas market. If you believe your property has been overassessed, a certified independent appraisal can be your strongest tool in a tax appeal.</p>

      <p>Our appraisers document the current market value of your property with precision, giving you credible evidence to present to the Clark County Assessor's Office. Even a modest reduction in assessed value can save homeowners hundreds of dollars per year.</p>

      <h2>How the Tax Appeal Process Works in Nevada</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>File an appeal with the Clark County Board of Equalization (deadlines apply — typically January each year)</li>
        <li>Submit supporting evidence, including a certified appraisal</li>
        <li>Attend a hearing before the Board if required</li>
        <li>Our appraisers can attend hearings and provide expert testimony if needed</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Fast, Lender-Compliant Turnaround</h2>
      <p>We know refinance timelines are tight. We offer priority scheduling and typically deliver completed reports within 2–3 business days of the inspection.</p>

      <div class="service-cta">
        <p>Available 7 days a week.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="tel:+17028949279" class="btn btn-primary">(702) 894-9279</a>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-secondary">Request a Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
